# <type>(<scope>): <summary>
#
# <body — why the change, not what>
#
# <footer — BREAKING CHANGE: ..., Refs: #123, ADR: docs/adr/NNNN-...md>
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# TYPE must be one of:
#   feat     — new user-visible feature
#   fix      — bug fix
#   docs     — documentation only
#   style    — formatting, no logic change
#   refactor — code restructure, no behavior change
#   perf     — performance improvement
#   test     — adding or fixing tests
#   build    — build system, dependencies
#   ci       — CI configuration
#   chore    — miscellaneous (lint config, tool setup)
#   revert   — revert a previous commit
#   data     — DVC-tracked dataset change
#   model    — DVC-tracked model change
#
# SCOPE (optional) is one of: ml, api, web, infra, docs, deps.
#
# SUMMARY:
#   - imperative mood ("add", not "added")
#   - no trailing period
#   - <= 72 characters
#
# BODY:
#   - explain WHY, not WHAT (the diff shows the what)
#   - wrap at 72 chars
#
# FOOTER:
#   - "BREAKING CHANGE:" for incompatible API / schema / model changes
#   - "ADR:" link when the change implements or changes a decision
#   - "Refs:" or "Closes:" issues
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
